   the chardack - greatbatch pacemaker    the chardack - greatbatch pacemaker used mallory mercuric oxide - zinc cells ( mercury battery ) for its energy source , driving a two transistor , transformer coupled blocking oscillator circuit , all encapsulated in epoxy resin , then coupled to electrodes placed into the myocardium of the patient 's heart .

inventions : it took dr. wilson greatbatch 2 years to develop this heart regulator first implemented in 1960

